@startuml
title QR/JSON Key Exchange
autonumber

actor "Initiator user" as UserA
participant "Initiator client" as A
collections "QR or JSON\nout-of-band channel" as OOB
participant "Responder client" as B
actor "Responder user" as UserB

UserA -> A: Create invitation for responder_id
A -> A: Generate exchange_id and ephemeral X25519 keypair
A -> A: Store local state with private key
A --> OOB: Share invitation payload only
OOB --> B: Import or scan invitation payload
B -> B: Validate protocol, version, role, TTL and participants
B -> B: Generate responder X25519 keypair
B --> OOB: Share response payload only
OOB --> A: Import or scan response payload
A -> A: Validate exchange_id, participants, roles and TTL
A -> A: Compute X25519 shared secret
B -> B: Compute same X25519 shared secret
A -> A: Derive session_key with HKDF-SHA256 transcript
B -> B: Derive session_key with HKDF-SHA256 transcript
A --> UserA: Show SAS from SHA256 transcript
B --> UserB: Show SAS from SHA256 transcript
UserA --> UserB: Compare SAS over independent channel
UserA -> A: Confirm matching SAS
UserB -> B: Confirm matching SAS
A -> A: Save key into local dialogue keyring
B -> B: Save key into local dialogue keyring

@enduml
